L12: citation_abstract: The branching fraction ratios of $\overline{B}^0	o D^+	au^-\overline{
u}_{	au}$ and $\overline{B}^0	o D^{*+}	au^-\overline{
u}_{	au}$ decays are measured with respect to their muonic counterparts, using a data sample corresponding to an integrated luminosity of 2.0 fb$^{-1}$ collected by the LHCb experiment in proton-proton collisions at $\sqrt{s} = 13$ TeV. The reconstructed final states are formed by combining $D^+$ mesons with $	au^-	o\mu^-\overline{
u}_{\mu}
u_{	au}$ candidates, where the $D^+$ is reconstructed via the $D^+	o K^-\pi^+\pi^+$ decay. The results are  egin{align*} R(D^{+}) &amp;= 0.249 \pm 0.043 \pm 0.047, R(D^{*+}) &amp;= 0.402 \pm 0.081\pm 0.085, \end{align*} where the first uncertainties are statistical and the second systematic. The two measurements have a correlation coefficient of $-0.39$ and are compatible with the Standard Model.
